<p>The <a href="https://marcsandersfoundation.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Marc Sanders Foundation</a> has announced its Philosophy in Media Fellows for 2025.<span id="more-53168"></span></p>
<p><a href="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025.png"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-53170 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025.png" alt="" width="1974" height="1349" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025.png 1974w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025-300x205.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025-1024x700.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025-768x525.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025-1536x1050.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/sanders-media-fellows-2025-400x273.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1974px) 100vw, 1974px" /></a></p>
<p>These are philosophers who were selected to take part in one of three funded summer programs&#8212;one on essay writing, one on trade books, and one on podcasting&#8212;that aim to &#8220;increase the presence of philosophy in print, audio, and video media by training philosophers to write and produce for the public, and by connecting philosophers to editors and commissioners in the media industry.&#8221;</p>
<p>The program is directed by <a href="https://profiles.ucr.edu/app/home/profile/barryl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Barry Lam</a> (UC Riverside, Hi-Phi Nation), and its faculty include writers and editorsÂ  of <em>The New Yorker</em> and <em>The New York Times</em>, editors from Viking Books and W.W. Norton, hosts and producers of successful podcasts, and others.</p>
<p>You can learn more about the program and this year&#8217;s fellows <a href="https://marcsandersfoundation.org/philosophy-in-media-2025/media-fellows-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/03/25/sanders-announces-new-set-of-philosophy-in-media-fellows/">Sanders Announces New Set of Philosophy in Media Fellows</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>